cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG

The paper deals with the security and privacy concerns in biometric verification systems, specifically in fingerprint recognition. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). The proposed method involves partitioning the fingerprint region and computing ridge-based features, which also relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of Cantor pairing function and random projection for cancelable template generation involves machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) techniques.
